description:
Surface burial in oblong wooden coffin.
Body supine, hands placed above the pelvis, head pointing NW.

Rect. shaft. Brick lined down to hard gebel. Chs. to N & to S. Plundered.
In shaft: Wooden hand fr. coffin, 4 bl. gl. fly amulets, Small discoid bl. gl. beads, Small bone disc.
In N chamber: poor bl. gl. scarab, Alab. kohl pot (no necl), Rough flint, Bone disc (as in shaft), Piece of flat alab. vase, Half of haematite kohl stick, 2 wooden kohl sticks, Wooden comb (poor condition), Copper callipers, Wooden Shabti similar to sev. found near a damaged burial near the shaft.

Small mud stoppers (12), Pottery group, Wood head rest.
In South chamber: Necklace of bl. gl. flies & beads, Piece bone inlay with [drawing], Copper callipers, Bl. Glass beads [drawing], Bl. gl. beads [drawing], Bl. gl. spindle [drawing], Piece of ivory bracelet, Carnel bead.
On top of shaft: Haematite kohl stick.
Shaft N.W-S.E.: 232 x 90 inside, Walls 30 thick, Bricking to 2.10 broken at top, Depth 4.15, Ledge of .10 a end of brick.

Rect. shaft. ch. to N & S. 
Deposits burnt by fire in shaft.
S. chamber: Wood hand, Piece bone inlay with [drawing], 2 dôm nuts, 3 figs, Alab. vase, Lid of another, Copper mirror & copper handle, Worked shell conus, Piece of stucko with gold leaf, Pottery, Rough ring of mother of pearl.
N. chamber: Pieces of 2 alab. Pepi jars, lid for one, Ivory wand shape of arm, Pieces of bone inlay as above, [...] knob in piece of bone, Large ivory (?) fly.

Shaft NW & SE
276 x 125 inside
Walls 46 thick.

Rect. shaft. Brick lined down to hard gebel
Shaft NW & SE. 278 x 97
Walls 45 thick.
Chamber at either end, badly plundered.
Pottery group.
In N chamber: Fragment of blue glazed bowl [drawing], Large numbers of very coarse mud whitened shabtis, Wooden beard.
In S chamber: Alabaster kohl pot [drawing], small stone vase [drawing], Blue glazed eye inlaid, one circular & one cylindrical bead, 1 shell bead, a large quantity of small rough shabtis showing traces of blue glaze.

Rect. brick-lined shaft. Plundered. Shaft NW & SE. A chamber at each end.
Large numbers of small badly [...] pottery shabtis showing traces of blue glaze, Long Blue bead in the form of a cat? [drawing], one circular blue & one cylindrical blue bead, spiral copper ring, Group of Pottery.

Plundered.
Rect. Shaft, brick lined down to hard gebel. Top of shaft broken away.
Shaft 276 x 113. Sides 38 thick. Depth 400.
One chamber at the NW.

Plundered.
Rect. shaft, brick-lined down to the hard gebel, top of shaft broken away.
Shaft 276 x 1.25. Brick sides 46 thick. Depth 480. Shaft NW & SE.
Small quantity of pottery.

Plundered.
Rect. Shaft, brick lined down to hard gebel, plastered on the inside with mud and whitened.
Shaft 270 x 105. Sides 32 thick. Depth 290. Shaft NW & SE.
One chamber at the N end.

Rect. shaft. Brick-lined with one chamber at the NW end.
Group of pottery.
Coffin & bones very much charred.

Plundered
Rect. shaft brick lined, chamber at either end. Shaft NW & SE.
In shaft & N chamber: A large number of small mud vases [drawing], Some dôm palm nuts, Three carnelian beads [drawings], portion of a haematite kohl sitck, an Inlaid eye, broken stone kohl pot [drawing], Pottery, one flint flake, one blue uninscribed scarab, Various blue beads one of this shape [drawing].
In S chamber: Group of pottery, Alabaster kohl pot [drawing], fragment of a haematite kohl stick, one shell.
See over
Ivory handle set in a copper grip [drawing]

Plundered.
Rect. shaft brick lined. Shaft NW & SE. At the N. end one chamber & two at the S end.
In the shaft were portions of ox skulls & several horns, one skull & one of the horns showed traces of red colouring.
Shaft 265 x 100.
A little pottery.

Plundered.
Rect. brick lined shaft. Shaft WNW by SE.
A few pieces of pottery.

Plundered.
Rect. shaft, brick lined, shaft NW & SE. Chamber at either end.

Plundered.
Rect. shaft, brick lined, shaft NW  & SE. Chamber at N only.
Two or three vase, a few small blue shabtis, three circular blue beads.

Plundered.
Rect. brick lined shaft. Shaft NW & SE.
Skull of a small rodent, A few vases, Nuts of [...] dôm palm.

Brick lined Rect. shat. Shaft NW & SE. A chamber at either end.
Traces of burning in both chambers.
A number of blue beads, Group of pottery, A number of marine shells three species, Two carnelian beads [drawing], Small blue beads [drawing], one blue glass bead.

Plundered.
Rect. brick lined shaft. Abandoned.

Plundered.
Rect. brick lined shaft. Shaft NW & SE.
Several skulls of a small rodent, head of a clay figurine [drawing], 1 small mud vase [drawing].

Plundered.
Rect. shaft, brick lined, shaft NW & SE. Chamber at N. end.
One vase with incised pattern [drawing].

Plundered.
Rect. brick lined shaft at a considerable depth below the surface, o
Fragment of two wooden hawks (painted), fragment of a coffin face covered with gold foil, One murex sp, Nuts of dôm palm, Two or three small mud vases, Some pottery.

Plundered
Rect. brick lined shaft. Shaft NW & SE
Abandoned dangerous

Plundered
Rect. brick lined shaft. Shaft NW & SE
Fragment of alabaster vase [drawing], Fragment of ivory

Plundered
Rect. brick lined shaft.
